---Rated via Beer Buddy for iPhone

Deep black solid liquid almost oily apperance, with a redish tone. Compact gingerbread head that vanishes quickly and leaves a thin coating. 
A smell of chocolate, snuff and burnt. 
The bitterness is distinctive bitterness that squeezes the tounge - not curling it. 
The Yeti is heavy, abit too heavy for my taste, soft, very little carbination, long taste. I dont feel any hint of alcohol, burnt, a bit smokey. A very powerful beer with alot of everyhing
